BRIEFINGC2M0_1 = "\cCGreat work collecting the \cFMayan artifacts\cC, \cPWilliam\cC. Thanks to you, \cQProf. Gutenberg\cC was able to find out what the \cRKrauts\cC are planning to do with them. \cRHitler\cC has established an excavation site overseas in \cBSouth America\cC at the \cBPyramid of Kukulcan\cC.";
BRIEFINGC2M0_2 = "\cCThe pyramid, built around 800 AD, is one of the greatest mysteries of the modern era. Its 365 stairs hinted at a mystical connection to Earth's time, but based on the latest research of Germany's greatest astro-physicists, the truth is terrifying.";
BRIEFINGC2M0_3 = "\cCSomewhere deep inside the pyramid, ancient powers have been awakened. Under control, these forces might be able to change the outcome of the war... not now, but a hundred years ago, or maybe even earlier. Yes, \cPWilliam\cC, \cFtime travel\cC.";
BRIEFINGC2M0_4 = "\cCIf \cRHitler\cC were able to lead his army through time, he would surely attempt to conquer the whole world before you are even born! If there is a time portal inside the pyramid, you must prevent the Nazis from activating it at all costs! Failure is not an option.";
BRIEFINGC2M0_5 = "\cCUnfortunately, \cQSgt. Douglas\cC has other duties to attend to, so he won't be coming with you on this mission. We have a captured U-boat waiting to take you to the excavation site. Grab all the equipment you can afford from \cQLt. Rojas\cC, and make haste! Godspeed, \cPWill\cC. Dismissed!";
BRIEFINGC2M0_6 = "\cCOooh, \cQGeneral Miller\cC is sending you to the \cBCaribbean\cC this time? Big waves, hot babes, lots of sun, and lots of fun! Man, you are so lucky, \cPWill\cC!";
BRIEFINGC2M0_7 = "\cCIf only I could come along with you for the ride... Oh, well. Our U-boat is waiting for you. Let's go!";

EPILOGUEC2 = "The winds of Iceland's winter blow in your face as \nyou reach the emergency tunnel's exit. Everything \nstill feels so unreal. \cQDouglas\cU is dead. \n\nYou can still remember the lazy days before the \nwar, when you joked about a future where you both \nended up in rocking chairs on a porch in rural South Carolina.\n\nThe hidden enemy was always nearby, but you weren't \nattentive; you never noticed he was there. And what \ndid you find down there? What is this \cFsword\cU, and what \nare the powers within? Was this what \cRHitler\cC \nwas after? \n\nYour thoughts are like fog, but there is one thing \nyou know for certain: On the death of your faithful \ncomrade and good friend, there is one thing you swear: \n\nYou will kill \cRJames Ryan \cUbefore the war ends, \nno matter what it takes.";
EPILOGUES2 = "Once more \cRGeneral Fettgesicht\cU was quicker,\nbut this time he's more thrifty with his words.\nIn an instant, one of his henchmen hits you with his rifle butt. \nThe first time isn't enough to knock you out, and half-conscious, you can\nhear the Nazis activate the portal. It's more \neffective the second time though...";

BRIEFINGC3M1_1 = "\cCWelcome back, \cPWill\cC. Sorry to hear about \cQDouglas\cC; my condolences. However, the war is still raging, and we have a job to do - we mustn't get preoccupied with our fallen comrades. \cRHitler\cC has launched the second phase of his \cRFinal Solution\cC: concentration camps.";
BRIEFINGC3M1_2 = "\cCThe \cRNazis\cC are bringing in thousands of Jewish prisoners into their death camps each day for the express purposes of gassing or enslaving them. \cQAllied High Command\cC has decided to send you in to shut down one of the worst camps: \cBDachau\cC in south Germany.";
BRIEFINGC3M1_3 = "\cCNow, the camp is too heavily guarded for us to throw our forces at it, but we believe the \cRNazis\cC will be caught off guard by an attack from the inside. You'll be going with the other prisoners on one of the trains bound for the camp, so you'll have no equipment or backup.";
BRIEFINGC3M1_4 = "\cCYou need to find a way inside, destroy the camp buildings, and free as many prisoners as possible before \cRHitler\cC's plans succeed. If you disable the Nazis' communications and steal a radio, \cQSgt. Ascher\cC will help you get past the guards and rescue the prisoners.";
BRIEFINGC3M1_5 = "\cCWe've also heard rumors about \cFsupernatural experiments\cC at the camp, and if they are true, it is imperative that you shut them down, and bring any \cFevidence\cC you find to \cQLt. Arlow\cC here at HQ. Now, go meet \cQSgt. Ascher\cC outside. Dismissed!";
BRIEFINGC3M1_6 = "\cCAll right, \cPCaptain\cC. By order of \cQGen. Miller\cC, I'll be the one sending you in, supporting you, and extracting you from the battlefield from now on. I know \cQCpt. Douglas\cC is irreplaceable, but in his memory, I promise I'll do my best!";
BRIEFINGC3M1_7 = "\cCI'll drop you off near the train station at 0800, and I'll update you as soon as you get a radio from the camp. Watch out for surprises, \cPCaptain\cC. \cBDachau\cC must be more than just an ordinary concentration camp if the rumors are true. Good luck, let's move out!";

BRIEFINGC3M2_1 = "\cCExcellent work liberating the prisoners from \cBDachau\cC, \cPWill\cC, but we have no time to lose! Our \cBBraunschweig\cC offensive is in shambles. We originally launched a three-pronged attack with our infantry, tank, and air divisions, but we badly underestimated the enemy forces.";
BRIEFINGC3M2_2 = "\cCAt 0620 hours, we received a distress call from Allied forces on the field. We do not know the status of our tank division, but our infantry have been pinned down by heavy fire from Nazi forces, and our planes are unable to breach the enemy's anti-air defences.";
BRIEFINGC3M2_3 = "\cCNow, our tank division may or may not be in one piece. However, we know you are qualified to serve on the crew of an \cFM4 Sherman\cC medium tank, so you are to replace any losses they've taken.";
BRIEFINGC3M2_4 = "\cCInsert Dialogue Here";
BRIEFINGC3M2_5 = "\cCHopefully, with your help, we'll be able to retake the battleground and turn the tide in our favour. Now, go meet Sgt. Nash outside - time is of the essence!";
BRIEFINGC3M2_6 = "\cCIt sounds like the Allied forces are in serious trouble out there.";
BRIEFINGC3M2_7 = "\cCInsert Dialogue Here";

BRIEFINGC3M3_1 = "\cCWelcome back \cPWilliam\cC, glad that you made but there is no time to have a breather now. We currently have a benefit due to your last efforts in central europe and if we act sharp, we will be able to kill two birds with one stone.";
BRIEFINGC3M3_2 = "\cCThe german front is still not breaking, mostly because our air reinforcements don't get past the heavily fortified Flak Towers near the borders of the Low Countries. The biggest treat is near the city of Arnheim in the Netherlands.";
BRIEFINGC3M3_3 = "\cCThe city is occupied by enemy forces and a hell of a place. We already tried to attack it several times but each time got beaten due to tanks and heavy cannonry stationed there. Instead of taking a sledgehammer to crack the nut, we have a better plan now which involves you.";
BRIEFINGC3M3_4 = "\cCYour job is to sneak through the town, find a way to the Flak Tower and kill the higher ranked members of the SS and sabotage the bunker wherever you can. The second goal is what you have been waiting for... your former camerade and traitor \cRJames Ryan\cC is hiding in the Flak Tower. He thinks he is safe from us, safe from you...";
BRIEFINGC3M3_5 = "\cCRevenge shouldn't be our impulse and personal hate not our duty. But for god's sake, he has to pay for his treason, and he has the pay for \cQDouglas \cC, one way or another.";
