CLERKCONV01 = "\cQLt. Laz Rojas";
CLERKCONV02 = "\cQHere you go!";
CLERKCONV03 = "\cGNice try, but you can't afford that.";
CLERKCONV04 = "\cCHell, \cPWilliam\cC, it's been a while! Didn't think I'd see you back in active duty, much less in the field! Glad you're here, though. I'll be honest - the situation ain't looking too good lately, so having you around should boost morale. The boys up top won't let me take part in active operations anymore, not since my injury, but I do my best to support HQ in other ways. We're low on munitions, because the damn \cRKrauts\cC attack our supply trucks! The good news is, I've been building a network to scrounge up certain supplies, so have a look! This stuff ain't free, though...";
CLERKCONV05 = "\cCLet's get to the point, \cPWill\cC. I see you've been busy piling up some loot, so why not buy something with it? I've scrounged up a few things here and there, you know. Here's what I've got for you:";
CLERKCONV06 = "\cCLeather Jacket \cU(50%) \cF$80";
CLERKCONV07 = "\cCFlak Jacket \cU(100%) \cF$160";
CLERKCONV08 = "\cCHeavy Armor \cU(200%) \cF$250";
CLERKCONV09 = "\cCGrenade \cU(1) \cF$50";
CLERKCONV10 = "\cCBackpack \cU(Ammo x2) \cF$250";
CLERKCONV11 = "\cCVitality Serum \cU(Max Health +5) \cF$75";
CLERKCONV12 = "\cCField Kit \cU(Health +25) \cF$100";
CLERKCONV13 = "\cCMine Detector \cU(makes mines visible) \cF$100";
CLERKCONV14 = "\cCWhat can you offer?";
CLERKCONV15 = "\cCTesla Shield \cU(100%) \cF$150";
CLERKCONV16 = "\cCHey, \cPWill\cC, come and take a look at this! Believe it or not, \cQGutenberg\cC actually made himself useful, the cranky old bastard! You brought something back from the future that he turned into a new type of armor. It can absorb all kinds of damage, for a while at least. Getting the raw material is a pain in the ass, so the armor ain't cheap, but it's worth it! See for yourself.";
CLERKCONV17 = "\cCNow I'm curious...";
CLERKCONV18 = "\cCBandages \cU(Health +1/sec., lasts 10 secs) \cF$25";
CLERKCONV19 = "\cC###TEXT AT THE BEGINNING OF CHAPTER 3, Laz Rojas welcomes back BJ, he is sad about the death of Dougles, has some words and also explains that during Astrostein they got their hands on new techniques (super shield), quite expensive but powerful future technolgoy###";
CLERKCONV20 = "\cCWhat's new in your stock?";
CLERKCONV21 = "\cCHell yeah, \cPWill\cC, nice to see you back and in the flesh! Not gonna lie, my friend, you had us worried as hell! I heard you had a rough time after you left for Tunis, but High Command didn't give us many details - just that you'd been captured and thrown in a Polish prison, and that the odds of us ever seeing you again were pretty slim.\n\n\cCBut you know I have my sources... is it true that you found it? The \cFStaff\cC...?\n\n\cCHa! Say no more - I knew my sources wouldn't disappoint me. But hell, if the enemy has it, all we can do is hope all the stories about its powers are just silly legends. Anyways, what can I do for ya, \cPWill\cC?";
CLERKCONV22 = "\cCWhat do you have for me?";
CLERKCONV23 = "\cCTotale Macht \cU(Health 100, Knife Berserk) \cF$200";
CLERKCONV24 = "\cCAdrenaline Kit \cU(Speed/Damage x2) \cF$250";
CLERKCONV25 = "\cCMine \cU(1) \cF$50";

MARINEAFTERDOUGLESCONV01 = "\cQSgt. Ascher\n\cCThis will be one of our finest hours. We won't get this close anymore, so let's do it for Captain \cQDouglas Blake\cC. Good luck, and may God be on our side as we fight.";
MARINEAFTERDOUGLESCONV02 = "\cQSgt. Ascher\n\cPCpt. Blazkowicz \cCcan you hear me? The Flaktower has fallen, the \cRKrauts \cCare sending in the final reinforcements for revenge and saving what can be saved. Get out now, we are waiting for you near the entrance.";
MARINEAFTERDOUGLESCONV03 = "\cQSgt. Ascher\n\cPCpt. Blazkowicz \cCfollow the General's recommendation and get yourself equipped first with powerful armament at the german command center in the west before you proceed south to the camp. Get our comerades out, they are counting on us!";
MARINEAFTERDOUGLESCONV04 = "\cQSgt. Ascher\n\cPCpt. \cCglad to hear you alive, we are on a good road! You need to sneak into the headquarter now. According to our informants, the back entrance is the best opportunity, it's guarded by only one person - with the noisy weather you can take him out with a single \cFKarabiner\cC shot.";
MARINEAFTERDOUGLESCONV05 = "\cQSgt. Ascher\n\cPCpt. \cC...\cU*kzzzrzzz*...\cCit you? The transm\cU*krzzrzzz*...\cChcan hear me, listen: The back entrance of the trainstation is little guarded...\cU*krzzzrzzz* \cC...sniper tower, kill the guar\cUkrzzzzrz\cC...better reception at the tower...\cUkrzzzzrzzz...\cC";
MARINEAFTERDOUGLESCONV06 = "\cQSgt. Ascher\n\cCGood work \cPCpt. \cC, all communications are offline. The SS can't call any reinforcements from now and are left on their own, but beware of the remaining \cRKraut\cC forces. Maybe find a \cFdifferent way\cC to get out instead of blasting through, maybe a red herring?";
MARINEAFTERDOUGLESCONV07 = "\cQSgt. Ascher\n\cCCareful from now on \cPCpt. \cC, try to sneak through this and destroy the radios before anyone sees you, and only use your shovel if there is the necessacity of killing someone. Alarms are everywhere. If you were spotted, it won't take long until the whole SS is here.";
MARINEAFTERDOUGLESCONV08 = "\cQSgt. Ascher\n\cPCpt. \cC, I expected more armory to be in the weapons chamber, but with this little amount of equipment you won't be able to shoot yourself out of the camp. Maybe you can use the \cFComp B\cC to blow something up to distract the guards from the main entrance. Do you remember the gas tanks near the west entrance of the camp?";
MARINEAFTERDOUGLESCONV09 = "\cQSgt. Ascher\n\cPCpt. \cC, whatever you have blown up, I felt the rumble to our current location. You must leave now, chaos is breaking lose and it is the best chance to escape just now, the SS is on its way and if they spot you, you are dead! So move!!!";
MARINEAFTERDOUGLESCONV10 = "\cQSgt. Ascher\n\cPCpt.\cC, it was him, \cRTotengräber\cC himself! It's not a good sign that the leading scientist and initator of the \cRThule\cC society is here. I knew there is more about the camp than the hq told us! ..and take the \cFPanzerschreck\cC with you!";
MARINEAFTERDOUGLESCONV11 = "\cQSgt. Ascher\n\cPCpt.\cC, what is this? The images.. experiments... this is terrifying! The dashboards - an example of what the supernatural powers of the \cFStaff\cC is capable of... I mean, reviving their fallen from death? Turning prisoners into some kind of weapon?...";
MARINEAFTERDOUGLESCONV12 = "\cQSgt. Ascher\n\cPCpt.\cC, I felt the ground rumbling, I hope...\cU*kzzzrzzz*... \cCfine! If you...\cU*kzzzrzzz*...this transmission, speed up and meet us at the gate to \cBDachau\cC, we need to leave this...\cU*kzzzrzzz*...until the \cRKrauts\cC are coming!";
MARINEAFTERDOUGLESCONV13 = "\cQSgt. Ascher\n\cPCpt.\cC, careful here! Our informants expect heavy resistance, do you have enough ammo and weapons to enter the catacombs?";
MARINEAFTERDOUGLESCONV14 = "\cQSgt. Ascher\n\cPCpt.\cC, to your right! I can see you!";
MARINEAFTERDOUGLESCONV15 = "\cQSgt. Ascher\n\cPCpt.\cC, the reinforcements are there, we have overrun the camp and freed the camp prisoners. Blow that damn thing up and get back to the gates to \cBDachau\cC.";
MARINEAFTERDOUGLESCONV16 = "\cQSgt. Ascher\n\cPCpt.\cC, this seems to be much worse than expected... it seems to be some kind of chemical refinery. Whatever this \cRZyklon C\cC is, you need to investigate further. Find clues!";
MARINEAFTERDOUGLESCONV17 = "\cQSgt. Ascher\n\cPCpt.\cC, freeing the prisoners and investigating the Zyclon C Refinery won't be enough - you need to destroy this no matter the cost. This is too dangerous to stay intact!";
MARINEAFTERDOUGLESCONV18 = "\cQSgt. Ascher\n\cPCpt.\cC, can you hear me? We jumped directly into an ambush! Rendezvous with us at the staging point. Check your compass for the exact position, and try to avoid enemy contact before you find some equipment --and hurry! We are under attack!";
MARINEAFTERDOUGLESCONV19 = "\cQSgt. Ascher\n\cPCPT.\cC, MAN THE MACHINEGUN, ON THE DOUBLE!";
MARINEAFTERDOUGLESCONV20 = "\cQSgt. Ascher\nPhew. All right, \cPCpt.\cC, we repelled their first attack, and we're safe for now. Come over here; we need to talk about our mission.";
MARINEAFTERDOUGLESCONV21 = "\cQSgt. Ascher\nTANKS INCOMING! GET THE PANZERSCHRECK, NOW!";
MARINEAFTERDOUGLESCONV22 = "\cQSgt. Ascher\n\cPCPT.\cC, we got report from our tank division: One of the tanks is still functional but covered by some Krauts. Use your advantage in the tower and sniper them down, then proceed east to the ank and recover it!";
MARINEAFTERDOUGLESCONV23 = "\cQSgt. Ascher\n\cCThe tank seems to be in a very good condition. Try to keep it like that when getting back to our base camp.";
MARINEAFTERDOUGLESCONV24 = "\cQSgt. Ascher\n\cCAll flaks have been destroyed, very good job \cPCpt.\cC, our C74 bombers will have much less danger when arriving.";
MARINEAFTERDOUGLESCONV25 = "\cQSgt. Ascher\n\cCThe Zyklon C tanks have been destroyed, \cPCpt.\cC, better chances for our Infantry units now.";
MARINEAFTERDOUGLESCONV26 = "\cQSgt. Ascher\n\cCThe communication has been destroyed \cPCpt.\cC, this should generate some trouble for the nazi command, the Kraut's won't be able to coordinate tank and flak attacks.";
MARINEAFTERDOUGLESCONV27 = "\cQSgt. Ascher\n\cPCpt.\cC, the cavalry is coming! Our B-24 bombers have arrived and will break the final resistance at \cBBraunschweig\cC. This is the moment of victory. Get back to our stand now, I am waiting for you to get out of this hell.";
MARINEAFTERDOUGLESCONV28 = "\cQSgt. Ascher\n\cPCpt.\cC, very good work! Destroying the radar central will baffle the enemy forces and stray them on the field. That way you will encounter less resistance.";

BJMESSAGE01 = "\cPWilliam Blazkowicz\n\cCIt's locked -- the padlock looks rusty, though. If only I had something to break it with...";
BJMESSAGE02 = "\cPWilliam Blazkowicz\n\cCI need another skull key to open that door. Maybe there's one lying around in this section of the catacombs?"; // C1M5

GENERALMCONV01 = "\cQGen. John H. Miller";
GENERALMCONV02 = "\cCWelcome back, \cPCpt. Blazkowicz\cC. We're prepared to commence our next operation. Are you ready to answer the call of duty?";
GENERALMCONV03 = "\cCBring'em On!";

RESISTANCEASK = "\cR???\n\cCHALT! WER IST DA?! DAS PASSWORT??? ...               ... oh, it's you, \cQCaptain\cC! Quick, entrez!";

MARINE1CONV01 = "\cQSgt. Nash";
MARINE1CONV02 = "\cC\cPCpt. Blazkowicz\cC, welcome back to HQ. How can I be of service?";
MARINE1CONV03 = "\cCWhat's the current situation?";
MARINE1CONV04 = "\cCWhere can I find my equipment?";
MARINE1CONV06 = "\cCWell, sir, we're short on munitions. Supplies should have arrived weeks ago, but most of them probably got intercepted by the \cRNazis\cC, and we'll need most of the equipment we have just to hold our position in the upcoming days. The staff will do their best to outfit you with a modest set of weapons and items for each operation. But if you have money, or something else to \cFbarter\cC with, \cQLt. Rojas\cC can sometimes get you useful odds and ends from his... sources. It's not much, but it comes in handy. Just check the Armory to your right.";
MARINE1CONV07 = "\cCAll I can say is this - be very careful, sir. \cRGerman soldiers\cC are quick and deadly. During missions, be aware of your surroundings, use cover to your advantage, and keep your weapons loaded. Listen for \cFradio transmissions\cC for important mission hints, updates on German troop movements, or urgent changes to the situation in the field. If you miss a transmission, simply check your \cU<console>\cC for a log file. Things have changed, sir; these operations will be very different from the combat experiences you've had before.";
MARINE1CONV08 = "\cCI understand.";
MARINE1CONV09 = "\cCI will take care, Sgt.";
MARINE1CONV11 = "\cCI will take care, Sgt.";
MARINE1CONV12 = "\cCWhat's the situation now?";
MARINE1CONV13 = "\cCArtificial Intelligence? Secret weapons?";
MARINE1CONV14 = "\cCYes, sir. When you shut down Operation Eisenmann, we managed to put a lid on the enemy's \cRmutant\cC reinforcements, but the \cRReich\cC seems to be making progress in other areas...\n\n\cCRumor has it that \cRHitler\cC's German labour front isn't just a trade union, but a research group developing secret weapons under the \cRThor's Hammer\cC project!\n\n\cCApparently, their weapons research has \cRtwo \cCmajor goals; people are saying one involves some kind of artificial intelligence, but the second, we can only speculate about.\n\n\cCOf course, I don't have the clearance for that kind of intel, but I suggest you catch up with \cQGeneral Miller \cCfor more details, Sir.";
MARINE1CONV15 = "\cCSir, things have only gotten worse in your absence. The German war machine is still rolling. \n\n\cCMutant armies, artificial intelligence, secret weapons - the Krauts are gaining strength thanks to their advances in science and technology. I don't see much hope for a free Europe, and I fear the worst for a free world.\n\n\cCThere are even rumors that \cRHitler\cC has found a powerful occult weapon in the deserts of \cBTunis\cC... but who knows? Allied High Command doesn't tell us much about all that. We're just soldiers, after all.";
MARINE1CONV16 = "\cCThank you, Sgt.";
MARINE1CONV17 = "\cCWhat's the current situation?";
MARINE1CONV18 = "\cCWhat has happened to the \cFSpear of Destiny\cC?";
MARINE1CONV19 = "\cCWhat has happened to \cRJames Ryan\cC?";
MARINE1CONV20 = "\cCWell, sir, the war is balancing on a knife's edge. It's not taking much longer for one side to win. Both sides have exhausted their forces, their morale is down to earth, and it's just a question of time when the war ends. The bad thing about it is that we just can't tell who will win and who will lose. It simply depends on the final lucky punch in a boxing fight over 12 rounds...";
MARINE1CONV21 = "\cCSir, it doesn't seem to be a secret anymore so I guess I can speak frankly. While we have been leading our efforts successfully against the \cRThor's Hammer\cC project, \cRHitler\cC and his scientists continued to examine the \cFSpear of Destiny\cC. Our intelligences didn't have good news at all.\n\n\cCThe spear does have some kind of supernatural powers. \cQProf. Gutenberg\cC is studying old files and books, and he is also examining the weapon you've found on \cPIceland\cC... don't ask, we all know about it. \n\n\cCSince \cQGeneral Miller\cC mostly ignored the spear, he is much carefuller now when it comes to any other artifact... certainly the Tunis operations opened his eyes. You should talk to \cQGutenberg\cC in the next days.";
MARINE1CONV22 = "\cCSir, our intelligences try to locate him for several weeks now since your last encounter but it's very hard actually.\n\n\cCHe most likely returned to Germany hiding his cowardly ass in a Nazi-bunker, but I can promise you one thing: We will blow him out of that!";

ASCHERCONV01 = "\cQSgt. Ascher";
ASCHERCONV02 = "\cCSir, when you're in the field, be aware of the most dangerous hazard out there - \cRlandmines\cC. You'll encounter two different kinds: the ones you can obviously see and easily avoid, and the buried ones, which can be deadly. A good way to locate buried mines is to crouch and watch for little bumps in the ground. Don't rush when you're avoiding them; be cautious and take your time! But if you have some cash, the best way to locate mines is to get yourself a \cFmine detector\cC from the Armory. Just keep an eye on the battery level.";
ASCHERCONV03 = "\cCSir, one thing worth mentioning: you may have already noticed, but the \cRJerries\cC sometimes store their equipment or other supplies in old wine barrels. Then they know where their stuff is and can find it quickly. But when they're expecting us to show up, they'll fill barrels with gunpowder and rig them as traps. The \cRKrauts\cC know which barrels have supplies and which are rigged, but they're impossible to distinguish. If you're low on ammo or health, the barrels are worth checking - just be careful!";
ASCHERCONV04 = "\cCSir, about those files you found back in \cBTunis\cC. We've analyzed them, and from what we've learned about the \cRNazi\cC excavation, their goal is to locate some kind of \cFancient artifact\cC. Their progress has been delayed, however, while the \cRNazis\cC search for a \cFkey\cC. We don't quite understand it, sir; the files seem to suggest they have one half of the \cFkey\cC, which they are guarding in \cBParis\cC while they search for the other half. It's all very odd. \cQProf. Gutenberg\cC has a theory that the dig must be related to the occult...";
ASCHERCONV05 = "\cCSir, that was a tough mission, and you were outstanding out in the field! If we keep scoring wins like this, we'll have the \cRNazis\cC on the run, and it'll be game over for them. Have you heard the latest? Rumor has it the \cRNazis\cC are searching for the \cFSpear of Destiny\cC now. They must be getting desperate. Whatever. Good luck on your next mission.";
ASCHERCONV06 = "\cCSir, welcome back to duty. We're all very glad to see you in one piece! Nobody else had ever broken out of a German prison before; you rescued \cQCpt. Ryan\cC from one, and now you've escaped from another on your own! That's twice you've proven that your reputation is more than justified.\n\n\cCSir, you've probably noticed that very few of the personnel here at HQ have been briefed in detail about your absence. Please remember, the details concerning the lost \cFStaff of Kings \cCand the situation in \cBTunis \cCare top secret; morale is low enough without word of these setbacks spreading through the ranks.\n\n\cQGen. Miller\cC will give you more details when the time comes. Until then, please use your discretion when people ask about your absence. \n\n\cCOh, and if anyone asks about what happened in the loo last month between the nurse and me - please be discreet about that as well.";
ASCHERCONV07 = "\cCSir, \cQGeneral Miller\cC has ordered me to brief you on what we know about \cRThor's Hammer\cC before you set out on your mission.\n\n\cRThor's Hammer\cC is the corporation responsible for the \cROperation: Eisenmann\cC research laboratory, the facility for the \cRautonomous killing machines\cC in the \cBBlack Forest\cC that you and \cQCpt. Ryan\cC destroyed in \cROperation: Feuerdrone\cC, and it's also the group behind the development of another powerful secret weapon we still only have little information about. \cRThor's Hammer\cC is the spine of \cRHitler's\cC war machine.\n\n\cCThe next step now is to cut off the snake's head in \cROperation: Schlangenkopf\cC. If we manage to kill two birds with one stone as the General says, it will be a critical blow to the Reich's war machine! I wish you the best of luck, sir.";
ASCHERCONV08 = "\cCSir, you may already have noticed, but different types of \cRUbersoldats\cC have different types of special attacks. The \cRSS Ubersoldat\cC can shoot a shrapnel grenade at you, in addition to his chaingun. The \cRAfrika Korps Ubersoldat\cC can throw grenades at you very quickly. Other \cRUbersoldat\cC variants have other types of special attacks."; // C2M4
ASCHERCONV09 = "\cCSir, be careful when you're fighting through the \cRStahlhimmel\cC facility. Intelligence has reports about an \cRelite infantry division\cC assigned to guard the \cRNazis\cC' most important assets. According to the intelligence reports, they're quick, tough, and they can throw grenades at you. However, they can be easily distinguished from other troops by their gas masks and long coats. Be careful when you happen to be up against these guys on the field."; // C2M5
ASCHERCONV10 = "\cCSir, we've heard rumors of a completely new Nazi infantry division, trained specifically to operate in the harsh cold environments of \cBNorway\cC and the \cBArctic Circle\cC. You may be up against these guys in the field on this mission."; // C2M6
ASCHERCONV11 = "\cCOkay then, \cPCaptain\cC! We've already cleared the area, so you check inside for any remaining forces. Oh, and grab some equipment before you proceed with \cQCpt. Blake\cC!";
ASCHERCONV12 = "\cCOh, thank God you made it, \cPCaptain\cC! Despite the horrific experiments you found under the camp, I'm glad you were able to do what you had to do.\n\n\cCI'll be blunt, \cPCaptain\cC. We were not expecting anything like this when we analyzed the Intel reports about this place. But now, it's clear that there is more to \cRHitler\cC's Final Solution than meets the eye.";
ASCHERCONV13 = "\cCWe need to get the prisoners out now. I got informed by the HQ that the 80th Infentery Division is already on it's way attacking the remaining Nazi-forces. You did a great job with that distraction of yours at the west end of the camp.";
ASCHERCONV14 = "\cCAccording the diagrams and blueprints you discovered at the headquarters, the crematorium, and the prison cellars, this place - as expected - is more than what we can see on the surface.\n\n\cCWe will need to decipher the files you found for exact details, but it doesn't take Albert Einstein to solve this puzzle:\n\n\cCThe Zyklon B gas used to kill the prisoners has been refined into some kind of biochemical weapon classified as \cRZyklon C\cC... the \cFSpear of Destiny\cC seems to have a role here as well. It seems to be much stronger and much more dangerous than the usual crap - maybe it does more than just kill you... but this is something for \cQLt. F. Arlow\cC to investigate; he is the one able to dechiffer the mystery, and we are the brawn.\n\n\cCHowever, one thing is clear: We need to destroy this refinery, it's too dangerous to leave it!";
ASCHERCONV15 = "\cCPrisoners and the concentration camp";
ASCHERCONV16 = "\cCZyklon C and the Spear";
ASCHERCONV17 = "\cCGeneral Totengräber";
//ASCHERCONV18 = "\cCYes, I know, you have already encountered him at the catacombs of the camp administration. \cRGeneral Totengräber\cC is the sick head of the SS and the extermination program, and he is a fucking coward - excuses for my words. You almost had him down at the garbage cellar, but don't give up: If we get him, we cut off the SS' head by one hit.\n\n\cCTime to hunt him down on his own playground now, and by chance, gather as much information about the Zyklon C as possible... and destroy what you can't carry. Good luck \cPCaptain\cC.";
ASCHERCONV18 = "\cRGeneral Totengräber\cC is the one you fought in the basement - and almost killed! But, of course, he had to run away from you, that cowardly son of a--\n\nAnyway, he is the head of the SS, and the manager of the gas chamber program. You're hunting him down on his own grounds now. If you kill him, the SS will lose it's head, and that's not all. Hopefully you can gather more information about that \cRZyklon C\cC stuff, or maybe even slow down the research by blowing up the facility. Good luck, \cPCaptain\cC.";
ASCHERCONV19 = "\cCCan you start again from the beginning?";
ASCHERCONV20 = "\cCSir, welcome to hell! The operation is already a total failure. \n\nWe had about fifty percent losses on our infantery troops, the \cRKrauts\cC have been well prepared for our arrival.\n\nOur tank division north from here has been ambushed and devastated, I can't get in contact with anyone of them, I fear the worst.\n\nThe B-24 support has been our joker, but the \cRFlak Bunker\cC at the north-west location is on higher ground and ruling the air space...\n\n Sorry for my phrasing but we are pretty fucked up.";
ASCHERCONV21 = "\cCWhat options do we have?";
ASCHERCONV22 = "\cCTogether with \cQLt. Anthony F. Arlow\cC I took a look at the tactial maps and instructions from \cQGeneral Miller\cC.\n\nIf we can break into the \cRFlak Bunker\cC and destroy its control units, we should be able to request the B-24 bomber to destroy the enemy's defensive fortification.\n\nHere is the exact location, check your compass and find a way to that bunker. Utilize the trenches and avoid the open-field. The germans have the strategical advance here!";
ASCHERCONV23 = "\cCSir, the \cRflak tower \cCwas only the peak of the iceberg.\n\nThis area has been partially cleared so far but our infantry divisions and frontlines break together in the east. We need to move on as quickly as possible, using the tank that you got and supporting our units before they get overrun. Follow the \cBtrack east\cC, we will catch up with the remaining forces later. Move on!";
ASCHERCONV24 = "\cCSir, we are in trouble now and it is important to act quickly until the enemy overruns us with his \cRStukas\cC and his \cRTiger Tanks\cC.\n\n\The situation is serious. If we want to win the battle for \cBBraunschweig\cC, we need to fight on 3 different places. But with the tank, our chances aren't that bad anymore. So, these are our mission goals:";
ASCHERCONV25 = "\cCCommunication Central";
ASCHERCONV26 = "\cCZyklon C Refinery";
ASCHERCONV27 = "\cCFlak Site";
ASCHERCONV28 = "\cCThe enemy's communication central is at the border of \cBBraunschweig\cC, the city in the north-west from here. There are only ruins left of it but the \cRKrauts\cC have entrenched theirselves with sniper units and even worse, some \cRPanzerschreck Wehrmacht soldiers\cC. Your tank is highly vulnerable against their attacks so you need to be carefully looking for these.\n\nIn one of the ruined buildings, a communication center has been established, from where the enemy coordinates air raids and tank attacks on the battlefield.\n\nFind the area, kill the staff members and destroy all com-tech that you find there.";
ASCHERCONV29 = "\cCThe Nazis are using \cRbio weapons\cC and \cRchemical gasses\cC to compensate their decreasing number of forces against our infantry units. We are loosing too many good man at the front, only a few divisions are holding their position.\n\nWe need to destroy their supplys to give our men a better chance when fighting against the Wehrmacht.\n\nIn the north-east, there is a large Zyklon C facility with \cR4 tanks\cC of concentrated gas. Get into that area and destroy the tanks.";
ASCHERCONV30 = "\cCWe still can't send in any of our B-24 bombers because of the \cRFlak Site\cC in the south-east from here. The Kraut's still have air advantage as long as these are functional.\n\nThe goal is to attack the site and destroy the \cRFlaks\cC but be careful, it is heavily guarded by some \cRTiger Tanks\cC as well as a huge amount of infantry units positioned at the main bunker that is also located there.";
ASCHERCONV31 = "\cPCPT., \cCTANKS AHEAD, FIRE!!!";

TALKINGTOILETCONV01 = "\cJToilet";
TALKINGTOILETCONV02 = "\cUsurprise, surprise: It doesn't answer.";
TALKINGTOILETCONV03 = "\cCC'mon, don't be shy.";
TALKINGTOILETCONV04 = "\cUSeriously, William, what the hell? You're really trying to talk to a toilet?";
TALKINGTOILETCONV05 = "\cCI'm just frustrated with the war and stuff...";
TALKINGTOILETCONV06 = "\cUAs if by miracle, the toilet flushes and begins to speak: \n\cCI am the almighty Toilet of Wisdom!";
TALKINGTOILETCONV07 = "\cCToilet of Wisdom";
TALKINGTOILETCONV08 = "\cCAs you probably know, each of your missions will involve a particular goal. This goal will be reflected in your \cFobjectives\cC, which you can view with the \cU<objectives>\cC key in the field. \cU*flush*\cC The \cFprimary\cC objectives are those that you must undertake to meet the mission's overall goal. The \cFsecondary\cC objectives, however, are optional - but if you accomplish them, you'll often be rewarded with supplies, money, and maybe more! \cU*flush*\cC They're worth the time and effort.";
TALKINGTOILETCONV09 = "\cCThat's technically two questions, but my enterobacteria levels are optimal today, so I will answer them anyway! \cU*flush*\cC Some areas may only be accessed through \cFvents\cC, so watch for vents that look weak. You can break through these with bullets or even your boot! \cU*flush*\cC If your eyes are sharp, you'll also notice \cFsuspicious walls\cC, behind which you can often find valuable things hidden away. That said, I'm not sure why anyone would hide their valuables behind suspicious-looking walls in the first place, but who cares what a toilet thinks, eh?";
TALKINGTOILETCONV10 = "\cCI want to know more";
TALKINGTOILETCONV11 = "\cCIn the field, you'll find small \cFNazi supply chests\cC scattered around. You'll need a \cFkey\cC to open them. They're filled with all kinds of useful stuff, so I recommend hunting them down. And if you find some toilet paper, bring it to me, eh? Yes... especially \cRtwo-ply... my precious!!\cC Er, I mean, uh, pardon me. \cU*flush*";
TALKINGTOILETCONV12 = "\cCWhat about objectives?";
TALKINGTOILETCONV13 = "\cCWhat about vents and suspicious walls?";
TALKINGTOILETCONV14 = "\cCWhat about chests?";
TALKINGTOILETCONV15 = "\cCYou have 4 questions to ask - choose them wisely! What do you wish to know?";
TALKINGTOILETCONV16 = "\cCWhat about bosses?";
TALKINGTOILETCONV17 = "\cCDuring your missions, you will not only encounter Nazi soldiers, but you will also see a few enemies who are much bigger and stronger than the other soldiers you face on the field. \cU*flush*\cC These guys are \cRbosses\cC. They're more or less cannonfodder with a higher military rank. Near the top of your screen, you will see their health bar and a swastika colored according their rank. \n\nLow-tier bosses are marked with a \cUsilver\cC swastika. You should be more careful when you encounter enemies marked with a \cFgold\cC swastika - these are the enemies' powerful leaders. But if you see a \cRred\cC swastika, you'd better be ready for HUGE problems - and I am not just talking about bloody diarrhea; \cU*flush*\cC that would be a charm compared to these ones.";

MISSINGC4 = "\cCYou don't have any \cGComp B explosives \cCwith you!";

