PAPERTEXT01 = "Cpt. Blazkowicz -\n\n  I hope you get this message! Very strange things have been happening during the day, and it's even worse at night. I cannot hold position here, so I will move on as soon as the night is over.\n\nThe sounds keep me awake. If I were to tell you about some of the things I've seen, you probably wouldn't believe me, so I'll just say this: Keep a fire burning, and don't go into the dark! We will catch up later, just head north.\n\n                    - Lt. Anthony F. Arlow\n\n\n\n\nP.S. - I've put some extra ammo in these barrels. You'll find some other leftovers from the Krauts in the area if you look around. Make sure you stock up!";
PAPERTEXT02 = "Leutnant Wagner, \n\n The picklock to the south-eastern watch tower is still in a very desolate condition. I am pretty sure it fells apart the next time Leutnant Bratwurst uses it with his thick hands. \n\nI advise you to take care of it in the next 3 days before some of the camp prisoners find out about it. I have the feeling they could easily break it with a shovel or even their bare hands if they look like Bratwurst's. \n\n - Obersturmbandfuehrer Knechtholz";
PAPERTEXT03 = "Cpt. Blazkowicz -\n\n  If you read this message, I will already have moved on. There are undead everywhere, zombies. Each night you stay at the same place, their number raises. It seems they feel your presence... they smell you. So try to not waste too much time.\n\n I have no idea what these brainless bastards are, but the seem to fear the light. The house gets its power from three generators scattered in the outside, but I don't have enough ammo left to look for them. If you are better equipped than I am, I have hidden a repair kit in the kitchen for you.\n\n The batteries of my flashlight seem to last for a few hours, so I will continue finding a save place somewhere. \n\n I already tried my luck north but some strange powers prevented me from moving on, so my next try is west from here, smoke is raising, maybe someone is still alive.\n\n Take care Cpt.                     - Lt. Anthony F. Arlow\n\n\n\n\nP.S. - The dead are dropping some kind of occult orbs,... with faces of death floating inside... I wasn't brave enough to touch them though. What are they? Are they of any use?";
PAPERTEXT04 = "Cpt. Blazkowicz -\n\n  This is a dead end, nothing else, damnit.\n\n I investigated the house but no-one was alive, just one of the undead I had to bring down. It was a nazi officer... or actually what has been left of him. It seems that things got out of control here.\n\n I have only little ammo left now, the flashlight is broken but I have found a lantern that I can carry.\n\n I also found some notes from the former officer that point me to an excavation site in the north-east of this wilderness. I will progress there and continue looking for some help or a save place. Keep track and.. stay alive!                     - Lt. Anthony F. Arlow";
PAPERTEXT05 = "Cpt. Blazkowicz -\n\n  I hope you get this message and are still alive. After proceeding through the caves, some areas collapsed and I wasn't able to return. I hope you somehow manage to get through this. \n\nStrange things are going on down under here, but this certainly seems to be the source of all evil, just as it has been on Iceland. Those evil energies the stones and the temples have seem to be the reason for the dead not finding any rest.\n\n The Nazis have been digging here for some time before everything got out of hands.\n\n The excavation site is huge, strange noises are everywhere, I have the feeling something is watching me just as I write this note. \n\n There is a second entrance in the east, I will try to to escape from there.\n\n We are close to the city, so keep up, we are almost save!                     - Lt. Anthony F. Arlow\n\n\n\n\nP.S. - I will leave some of the ammo for you, so you can stock up!";
PAPERTEXT06 = "Dear Schatzilein, \n\n something strange was happening this night. My comerades Franz and Gustav came from the excavation last night, totally exhausted. Franz told me that something went wrong down there. \n\nDoctor Schabbs Jr. who is leading the excavation left the place already in a hurry, he even forgot to take his equipment with him. \n\nThe workers are still down there digging, as well as a few scientists who live in the mansion, but... they seem to be kinda nervos, but nobody is telling is anything.\n\n I will continue my work tomorrow, I am sure things will get relaced until then.  \n\n - Dein Heinrich";
PAPERTEXT07 = "Dear Schatzilein, \n\n I am not sure if we will ever meet again... they are everywhere, dead workers, undead... flesh-hungry... I have no idea what they are, Franz is one of them... \n\n I tried to talk to him, stop him... I had to shot him, my friend Franz... I am sitting here now in the ...cellar of this house... a cellar full of torture, what is this here?... blocked up doors, no chance for escape... they are coming for me.. I love you Schatzilein!  \n\n - Dein Heinrich";
PAPERTEXT08 = "Announcement of the Dig staff:\n\nProceed with extreme caution and take your light source with you when entering the excavation site from this entrance: The cave area is very fragile. We recommend to enter from the entrance at the city plaza.  \n\n - Obersturmbandfuehrer Knechtholz";
PAPERTEXT09 = "Doktor Schabbs Jr., \n\n The research results on the new mutant base aren't what the Fuehrer has expected. In a letter with highest priority, he told me that the following issues are inacceptable: \n\nThe jewish specimen are currently not controllable after their metamorphosis. Obviously the balance between the minerals we found on Iceland and the occult powers of the Spear of Destiny isn't regulated yet.\n\n A solution is demanded by the Fuehrer within the next two months, the Final Solution needs to be a full success to destroy the enemies morale.    \n\n - General Totengraeber";
PAPERTEXT10 = "William my friend, \n\n I write this letter as a reminder of what I need to tell you after we return from Trondheim. I have no idea, maybe I am oversuspicious but I want you to listen: Don't trust Cpt. Ryan. Or at least stay wake.\n\nI know I am not allowed to read the protocols at the hq, but I did...\n\nRemember the surprising ambushes, the randomly activated alarms during your missions? Every single time, Cpt. Ryan was involved in the briefing or part of the mission... this is no surprise, I fear the worst, my friend.\n\nI can't reveal that information now, the Operation Hades is too important, but Will, we need to talk to the General as soon as we are back. Ryan is dangerous, William, we must not underestimate him, not even if we really reveal his true identity...\n\nI hope this all is over soon, I want those lazy days so hard... both of us in rocking chairs on a porch in rural South Carolina.\n\n  - Sincerely Douglas";
PAPERTEXT11 = "Mon ami,\n\nI have left to ren-dez-vous with Allied reinforcements. Remember: you're looking for an ancient solar disc. The mysterious door next to my hideout leads to the Paris catacombs. Once you've found the key for that door, scour \n\nAlso, I had better see you defending the Nebelwerfer once I come back, or else I will have Gen. Miller court martial you for insubordination!\n\n  - J. Bertrand"; // Juliette, C1M5